 Q. (Inaudible.)
 PHIL MICKELSON: Winning a major makes the year special. I was trying to do something here. I was trying to get a little greedy and see if I could get a second one. 
 Unfortunately, it didn't play good enough golf. Had a fun week though. I really enjoyed my time here in Wisconsin. Whistling Straits is a wonderful course and I guess we're going to have some more big championship venues here and I think that's great. I think that's great.

 Q. Seems like you made a lot of news this week as well. Just kind of a wild week just in general for you?
 PHIL MICKELSON: It has been. Yeah, it has been. But I had a good day today and take a little bit of momentum from it and I'm looking forward to starting our FedExCup, our playoffs with the Barclays in a week and hopefully I'll have my game sharp and ready to play.

 Q. The medications helping you today?
 PHIL MICKELSON: Yeah, I feel great. After just over two weeks of treatment I feel great. I don't feel like there's anything wrong right now. I've been fortunate so far, I just hope that it -- I still react as well as I have to the meds.

 Q. The Top-8 will be set forth end of the day. Nick and Dustin both have a real strong chance of making it there. Talk about the makeup of the team with the new guys?
 PHIL MICKELSON: We're going to have a lot of new blood on this team because I expect Watney to be on the team and Dustin to be on the team and with Jeff Overton already there and we have got other young players with Hunter Mahan and Anthony Kim even though they have some experience already, we're going to have a very young yet a young team and with Kuchar being on as well. And there's some other players that are young that I think would be very good picks too. I think Ricky Fowler would be a great pick for us. Because he's just got such a solid game that to get him in the mix right away would be great for American golf. 
 But I don't know with so much youth if that's what Pavin wants to do, I don't know. I'm not trying to lobby, I'm just saying we have a lot of good young players in America that are going to add a lot of value to the team. 

